President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Ward Brehm for the position of Member of the Board of Directors of the African Development Foundation. Brehm is the Founder and Chairman of The Brehm Group, an insurance consulting firm based in Minneapolis, Minnesota. He has been a member of the Board of Directors of the African Development Foundation since October 2010 and previously served as Chairman from 2004 to 2008. Brehm has been recognized for his work in Africa and was awarded the Presidential Citizens Medal. He has also been involved with the Pilgrim Center for Reconciliation, a program that supports victims and perpetrators of genocide in Rwanda and Burundi, since 1995. In addition, Brehm initiated the Windpump Project in 1993, which brought clean water to remote areas in Kenya. He has authored two books on his experiences, titled "Life Through a Different Lens" and "White Man Walking." Brehm holds a B.A. from the University of Minnesota.